<h2 id="principle">Principle</h2>

<p>
We build upon, and improved, a combinatorial (sequential) single-molecule 
fluorescence in-site hybridization (smFISH) approach. Our proprietary 
transcript-specific probes are designed to color-code targeted genes 
of interest in several rounds of hybridization and 3D-imaging (z-stacks) 
with a unique encoding scheme.
</p>

<p>
Other key features are reliable detection of very rare transcripts, 
exquisite resolution, and the possibility to post-procress 
the sample, e.g. using standard cell labeling with antibodies or dyes, 
which make the genexyz system play in a league of its own.
</p>

