<h3>Preparation</h3>

<p>
Before starting a run on the instrument, a sample needs to be treated in a special way, 
and gene-specific probes need to be attached.
</p>

<h4>Gene Panels</h4>

<p>
We offer standard gene panels for certain applications, but also provide an online interface
for fully customized panel design to exactly match your research needs. 
The list of species we offer designs for (in addition to <strong>human</strong> and 
<strong>mouse</strong>), and more details are given directly on the design-interface page.
</p>

<h4>Fixation & Hybridization</h4>

<p>
The first step of sample-preparation comprises of the <strong>fixation</strong> of the sample 
(tissues or cell cultures) to a special microscope slide which we will provide for your 
type of sample, followed by the <strong>hybridization</strong> of the gene-specific probes.
</p>

