<h3>Processing</h3>

<p>
After mounting the sample on the instrument, a setup-wizard will 
guide through sample naming, region selection and assignment of 
probe-sets used for each well.
</p>

<p>
During the run, multiple rounds - typically eight - of 
<strong>colorization</strong>, <strong>imaging</strong>, 
and <strong>decolorization</strong> of the 
probes are performed. This process will take around three days to complete, 
depending on the number of samples and regions that are being imaged.
This process will be fully automized by our <strong>genexyz</strong> platform.
Microscopic data capture and subsequent image analysis occurs on-the-fly.
</p>

